"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-27-hero-security-guard-wrongly-accused-planting-a-bomb-olympics-21287259\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"On a hot July evening inAtlanta, Georgia, crowds of people were gathered in Centennial Olympic Park on the eighth day of the 1996 SummerOlympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33, \"end\": 40, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\", \"score\": 0.9999999859887795, \"rank\": 1.0952459720751624e-08, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thirty-three-year-old Richard Jewell had been more than seven hours into his shift as a security guard in the area when he noticed something odd.\", \"from\": 147, \"to\": 292, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 169, \"end\": 183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Jewell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3549600624030532e-65, \"text\": \"Richard Jewell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Jewell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Jewell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A green military-style bag had been left unattended and nobody was claiming it.\", \"from\": 294, \"to\": 373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jewell raised the alarm, and minutes later, 911 received a call from aphonebooth near the park.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 469, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'There is a bomb in Centennial Park.\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You have 30 minutes.'\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 529, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jewell began moving people away and out of the park, but at 1.20am, the 40-pound pipe bomb exploded - killing one woman and injuring more than 100 others.\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The unsuspecting security guard saved many lives that day by spotting the bag and beginning evacuations.\", \"from\": 687, \"to\": 791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But even though Jewell was praised as a hero following the bombing, the narrative slowly shifted.\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Within days, Jewell - a quiet security guard who lived with his mother - became a suspect in the 1996 Atlanta Olympic bombings.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 1018, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jewell was born in Danville, Virginia, to a father who worked for Chevrolet and a mother who worked in insurance.\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1049, \"end\": 1057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia\", \"score\": 0.9999967296165595, \"rank\": 3.0214206742636477e-06, \"text\": \"Virginia\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia\"}, {\"begin\": 1086, \"end\": 1095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chevrolet_Indy_V6\", \"score\": 0.6712214246782418, \"rank\": 0.48981467068688855, \"text\": \"Chevrolet\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chevrolet_Indy_V6\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chevrolet_Indy_V6\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He moved to Atlanta with his mum and stepfather when he was young.\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1146, \"end\": 1153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2411114665928466e-26, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He worked in a variety of jobs before joining the Habersham County Sheriff's Office in Georgia as a jailer in 1990.\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1289, \"end\": 1296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\", \"score\": 0.9999999859887795, \"rank\": 1.0952459720751624e-08, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was charged with impersonating a police officer after arresting a couple when he was working as a security officer.\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jewell, described as an 'overzealous' employee, eventually resigned and worked a brief stint as a campus police officer, before returning to Atlanta and getting a job as a security officer ahead of the 1996 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1579, \"end\": 1586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2411114665928466e-26, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While working in that job, he spotted the backpack which turned out to be a massive pipebomb, which exploded in the park, killing one woman and injuring more than 100.\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jewell's attempts to move crowds away from the area saved countless lives on July 27, 1996, and he was praised for his efforts.\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1957, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But all of that changed with one headline from The Atlanta Journal three days later.\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 2042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2005, \"end\": 2024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlanta_Journal-Constitution\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Atlanta Journal\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlanta_Journal-Constitution\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlanta_Journal-Constitution\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the days following the bombing, Jewell had not been considered a suspect by the FBI.\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2127, \"end\": 2130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2523786338705633e-47, \"text\": \"FBI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 28, they received a call from the president of Piedmont College, where Jewell had worked briefly as a campus security guard.\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2187, \"end\": 2203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piedmont_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Piedmont College\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piedmont_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piedmont_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He told the FBI that Jewell could have been involved in planting the bomb.\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2277, \"end\": 2280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2523786338705633e-47, \"text\": \"FBI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 30, three days after the bomb detonated, The Atlanta Journal published an article titled 'F.B.I.\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2390, \"end\": 2409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlanta_Journal-Constitution\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Atlanta Journal\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlanta_Journal-Constitution\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlanta_Journal-Constitution\"}, {\"begin\": 2439, \"end\": 2445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0660066664884243e-44, \"text\": \"F.B.I.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Suspects 'Hero' Guard May Have Planted Bomb.'\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2491, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The newspaper did not cite its sources for the article, but it sparked a media firestorm - camera crews and reporters camped outside of Jewell's home in the days following the allegation.\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2680, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Why did they latch onto the idea that a security guard planted the bomb to become a hero?\", \"from\": 2682, \"to\": 2771, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A case less than ten years earlier saw a volunteer firefighter in California set intentional fires to put them out, in order to be a 'hero'.\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2838, \"end\": 2848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999999988740456, \"rank\": 1.126021295816889e-09, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 29, the FBI was advised that 'Jewell fit the profile of a person who might create an incident so he could emerge as a hero.'\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 3046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2930, \"end\": 2933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2523786338705633e-47, \"text\": \"FBI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, he was considered a suspect - but not the only one.\", \"from\": 3047, \"to\": 3103, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the idea of a man who helped save lives in the bombing being the man who actually planted it was a juicy news story - and most news organisations ran with it.\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3267, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For Jewell, he had begun his '88 days of hell'.\", \"from\": 3269, \"to\": 3316, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was unable to leave his apartment without being swarmed by reporters and cameras.\", \"from\": 3317, \"to\": 3401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Three months after the damning headline claiming Jewell may have planted the bomb in Atlanta, his name was cleared.\", \"from\": 3403, \"to\": 3518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3488, \"end\": 3495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2411114665928466e-26, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Justice Department wrote to Jewell's lawyer that he was not the man they believed to be behind the bombing.\", \"from\": 3520, \"to\": 3631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3524, \"end\": 3542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Department_of_Justice\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.586260930487042e-13, \"text\": \"Justice Department\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Department_of_Justice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Department_of_Justice\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jewell's name was cleared - but his reputation was never the same, despite being the actual hero of the Olympic bombings.\", \"from\": 3633, \"to\": 3754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He won multiple lawsuits against NBC, CNN and the New York Post.\", \"from\": 3756, \"to\": 3820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3789, \"end\": 3792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0191724284968655e-15, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He went on to work small jobs in Georgia law enforcement.\", \"from\": 3821, \"to\": 3878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3854, \"end\": 3861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\", \"score\": 0.9999999859887795, \"rank\": 1.0952459720751624e-08, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Months after his name was cleared, Jewell told The New York Times: 'I am a lot more cynical than I used to be.\", \"from\": 3880, \"to\": 3990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3927, \"end\": 3945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7345478066912156e-18, \"text\": \"The New York Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not as trusting as I once was.\", \"from\": 3991, \"to\": 4026, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I do not think I am as outgoing as I used to be.'\", \"from\": 4027, \"to\": 4080, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jewell went on to marry his wife Dana in 1998 and remained with her until he died of heart failure and side effects of diabetes.\", \"from\": 4082, \"to\": 4210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4115, \"end\": 4119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dana_Scully\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.268211762405475e-28, \"text\": \"Dana\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dana_Scully\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dana_Scully\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though he was truly one of the heroes of the tragic 1996 Olympic Bombings, he wasn't the man who planted the bomb which killed a woman and injured hundreds.\", \"from\": 4212, \"to\": 4368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That man wasn't caught until 2003, after bombing two other locations.\", \"from\": 4370, \"to\": 4439, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Eric Robert Rudolph was the lone wolf behind the deadly Atlanta bombing on July 27, 1996.\", \"from\": 4441, \"to\": 4530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4441, \"end\": 4460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Rudolph\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eric Robert Rudolph\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Rudolph\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Rudolph\"}, {\"begin\": 4497, \"end\": 4504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2411114665928466e-26, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was first named as a suspect in February 1998.\", \"from\": 4532, \"to\": 4581, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Eventually, the bombings of a north Atlanta abortion clinic and a gay nightclub were linked to Rudolph - as well as the Olympic bombing, and one in Alabama.\", \"from\": 4582, \"to\": 4738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4618, \"end\": 4625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2411114665928466e-26, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}, {\"begin\": 4677, \"end\": 4684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudolf_I_of_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9255711891193825, \"rank\": 0.080193925603598, \"text\": \"Rudolph\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudolf_I_of_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudolf_I_of_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 4730, \"end\": 4737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alabama\", \"score\": 0.9999999803349058, \"rank\": 1.963697709598066e-08, \"text\": \"Alabama\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alabama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alabama\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bombing in Centennial Olympic Park was the first time Rudolph detonated one of his explosives and the largest.\", \"from\": 4740, \"to\": 4854, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4798, \"end\": 4805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudolf_I_of_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9255711891193825, \"rank\": 0.080193925603598, \"text\": \"Rudolph\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudolf_I_of_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudolf_I_of_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was also the person who made the phone call to police, warning them about the bomb just minutes before it detonated.\", \"from\": 4855, \"to\": 4974, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was put on the top ten most wanted fugitives list in May 1998 but was on the run for five years until he was found rummaging through a trash bin in Murphy, North Carolina in 2003.\", \"from\": 4976, \"to\": 5158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5127, \"end\": 5149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murphy,_North_Carolina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Murphy, North Carolina\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murphy,_North_Carolina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murphy,_North_Carolina\"}, {\"begin\": 5127, \"end\": 5149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murphy,_North_Carolina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Murphy, North Carolina\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murphy,_North_Carolina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murphy,_North_Carolina\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rudolph pleaded guilty to the charges and is serving multiple life sentences without the possibility of parole.\", \"from\": 5160, \"to\": 5271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5160, \"end\": 5167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudolf_I_of_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9255711891193825, \"rank\": 0.080193925603598, \"text\": \"Rudolph\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudolf_I_of_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudolf_I_of_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Atlanta bombing, while shocking and tragic, was not the deadliest attack made during the Olympics.\", \"from\": 5273, \"to\": 5375, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5277, \"end\": 5284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2411114665928466e-26, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1972, the deadliest terror attack at the Olympic Games happened in Munich, when 11 Israeli athletes and coaches were killed by members of the Palestinian group Black September.\", \"from\": 5377, \"to\": 5556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5447, \"end\": 5453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\", \"score\": 0.9999932224525339, \"rank\": 6.765132492170551e-06, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\"}, {\"begin\": 5463, \"end\": 5470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 0.99933219204278, \"rank\": 0.0006682380196816041, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}, {\"begin\": 5522, \"end\": 5533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999985225710588, \"rank\": 1.434279510959838e-06, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dubbed the 'Munich Massacre', the group infiltrated the Olympic Village where the athletes were staying before breaking into the building and taking the Israeli team hostage.\", \"from\": 5558, \"to\": 5732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5614, \"end\": 5629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1433440857313727e-29, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 5711, \"end\": 5718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 0.99933219204278, \"rank\": 0.0006682380196816041, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the situation was ongoing, the games did not stop.\", \"from\": 5734, \"to\": 5790, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"West German police eventually intervened and killed five of the eight terrorists, but all of the hostages were killed in the process.\", \"from\": 5792, \"to\": 5925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5792, \"end\": 5810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Police_(Germany)\", \"score\": 0.9999999977944753, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"West German police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Police_(Germany)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Police_(Germany)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since then, moments of silence have been observed at some Olympic ceremonies for the deceased athletes who were meant to compete in 1972.\", \"from\": 5927, \"to\": 6064, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get in touch with our news team by emailing us atwebnews@metro.co.uk.\", \"from\": 6066, \"to\": 6135, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6123, \"end\": 6134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"score\": 0.9993608704168107, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"metro.co.uk\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our news page.\", \"from\": 6137, \"to\": 6184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Olympics 2024 timetable: Full day one schedule in Paris  ArrowMORE:Heathrow and Eurostar hit by mass cancellations as M5 sees two-hour delays  ArrowMORE:How does the Olympic diving scoring system work and how many rounds are there?\", \"from\": 6186, \"to\": 6427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6246, \"end\": 6251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.265442814272835e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6276, \"end\": 6284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 4.828586566772909e-12, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Never miss the biggest stories with breaking news alerts in your inbox.\", \"from\": 6429, \"to\": 6500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 6502, \"to\": 6591, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\", \"from\": 6592, \"to\": 6652, \"entities\": []}]}"